    <name>Assignment #1: Reflect with students on goals and progress</name>
    <intro>&lt;p&gt;An important part of self-regulated learning is setting goals. Watch this video to help you introduce self-regulation to your students and encourage them to set goals and track their progress.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;iframe height="360" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Xay8jR8z_hY?rel=0" frameborder="0" width="480" allowfullscreen=""&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;[&lt;a title="PDF, opens in new window" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/transcript.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;Transcript&lt;/a&gt;]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use this short slide show on YouTube to introduce the topic in class.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: bold;"&gt;Discuss:&lt;/span&gt; Where else or in what other contexts have you or your learners set and tracked goals? How did you/they do it? Did it help you/them reach the goal?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Write a two-to-three paragraph reflection of how you might help your students to set goals and monitor their progress (click Edit my submission).&lt;a href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/transcript.pdf"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
